De_horseshoe is a medium sized defuse map with 2 bomb sites.

Bomb site A located by the horse statue next to CT spawn.
Bomb site B located by 'headless' statue in the central court yard.

BSP Map file includes:-
Nav file.
Map overview for spectators.
Rader overview for players.
All areas are named and have ambient sound.
Spawns for 17 per side.

Hope you enjoy. Please comment and rate if you download.

*********************************** Counter-Strike: Source *********************************** TITLE: CS:S Map - de_home4holidays AUTHOR: SM Sith Lord E-MAIL: smsithlord@yahoo.com WEBSITE: http://www.sithmercenaries.net FILENAME: de_home4holidays.bsp FILESIZE: 13.8 MB DATE RELEASED: December 23rd, 2006 AUTHOR: SM Sith Lord (smsithlord@yahoo.com) DESCRIPTION: Merry Christmas! You've returned to the scene of de_DomesticDispute, but this time its in the middle of a snowy blizard and santa has come and left the xmas cheer all over the place. You can see santa and his sleigh flying away from T spawn at the start of each round, if you're quick enough! CT's camp the crime scene (house) while T's try to destroy the evidence (waboom). If T's take too long to blow up evidence, the panic room unlocks and the CT's can escort the witness to safety to win. WARNING: Due to the layout of this map, it is intended for high-performance machines. Running it on a slower machine will result in unsatisfactory framerates in some spots. BUGS: * The snow falls even inside the house. Just think of it as magic xmas dust! * Nav mesh still isn't perfect, and bots can still see thru some objects they shouldn't. NOTICE: It has come to my attention that there is no working .nav file included within the bsp. Until I fix this problem, you can download the .nav file seperately by clicking here.

"First off, I am extremely grateful and pleased to my relatives. Next, I would like to show appreciation to one and all at Mapcore community for the helping service and great support.

I never had in my mind that I would accomplish somewhat in level design.
The works on the map have been awe-inspiring shit, the best thrill and the longest voyage, but also the most horrible nightmare and the worst sting in the neck.

As a final point, I’m glad that I have this sheltered and completed.
This entire project mission supposed to be improved in design, detail and graphics, but I reached the half life two engine restrictions and limit to the last part.

So it did not turn out well, as it was supposed to be… But I’m still swollen with pride of it, a large amount of time into this development, all the power and the - throw away of life.

In conclusion it’s done. I prooved myself. But I still dont. "

de_highrise by Diamante "X-tr3m3r" Pasotti This map was made for the Realistic Mapping Contest but it is optimized and fully playable. STORY: Terrorists have attacked a highrise building in order to bomb it. The surrounding areas have been evacuated and there is a four-block quarantine for fear that the Terrorists could use bio-bombs. The map features: *HDR *Soundscapes *Overview *Hand-Tuned Nav file *Various Custom Content *40 Player Spawns *2 Bomb Sites It took me about 3 months to develop this project. It has 100 direct lights, 9583 faces, 8 displacements and lots of time and coffee. Compile times: vbsp = 16 seconds vvis = 23 minutes, 13 seconds vrad = 1 hour, 44 minutes, 48 seconds + 1 hour, 51 minutes, 20 seconds Total = 3 hours, 59 minutes, 37 seconds It's layout is similar to the layout of the rooftop of the Mercy Hospital from Left 4 Dead. However it has tons of differences as you can see from the screenshots. Many thanks to everyone who contributed in the creation of this project especially Nay0r. If I'm forgetting to credit any tester, please notify me. HAVE FUN!!! Also, if you liked the map and think that I've done a good job with it or appreciate the fact that I've put lots of effort into this, vote for me as Mapper of the Month. Check the votebox in my profile Oh and obviously, this is compiled for CS:S. :) Many thanks to Mini for the video The song heard in the video is: "Late Nights and Street Fights" by Dirty Vegas ***UPDATE 02/04/2009*** Thanks to Chizbone the nav file is now way better. If you liked the map, please download the new version. Thanks!

de_hiekkasauna - Final V1 (???)
-
It's not really a final version if it is V1? Eh, it doesn't matter.
Even though this is my first map uploaded to GB, it's not my
first map. I've made around 3-4 little test maps (for CSS)
that I haven't released _anywhere_. I also have released
A3 of a TF2 arena map to TF2Maps (Look for it! arena_kaboom)
So I do have small experience of Hammer. :P
As for gameplay, you know the drill - CTs spawn at the cottage
(where the sauna is) and they have to protect the sauna from
the T's who are going to blow the whole place up
(I don't think this scenario has ever made sense. Why are
they going to blow the sauna up?)

Anyway, the credits:
--
-Zabidenu (me) for making the map

-Komaokc for the awesome skybox texture

-Pelihalli for having an AWESOME sauna map server!

-Sedaix and Fhindu for detail critique

--
As for installing,
--
simply drop it to your 
Steam\steamapps\*USERNAME*\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps
folder.

--

Well, that was it! Now go play it and have fun!
--
